description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8772/documentation

The dataset can be used as conductive salt for a lithium-ion battery. Data are based on patents. For infrastructure, the ecoinvent dataset "chemical plant, organics" is accounted. Transportation efforts are based on ecoinvent standard estimates.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



This dataset includes the reaction of lithium fluoride, phosphorous pentachloride and hydrogen fluoride in an autoclave to lithium hexafluorophosphate and hydrogen chloride. Conversion factor for lithium  is 86.7%. The reaction temperatur is -78°C. Assumption: Cooling happens with a heat pump (coefficient of performance = 1.5). Neutralisation of hydrogen flouride and hydrogen chloride with potassium hydroxide. Phosphorous trifluoride is proxy for phosphorous pentafluoride for emission to air. Transports according to ecoinvent standards.For infrastructure, the ecoinvent dataset "chemical plant, organics" is accounted.
